=== Titles and styles ===

* '''1 December 1831&amp;nbsp;– 4 February 1853''': ''Her Highness'' The Princess Dona Maria Amélia of Brazil

=== Honors ===

Princess Maria Amélia was a recipient of the following Brazilian Orders:

* Grand Cross of the [[Order of Pedro I]].{{sfn|Laemmert|1849|p=24}}
* Grand Cross of the [[Order of the Rose]].{{sfn|Laemmert|1849|p=24}}

She was a recipient of the following foreign honors:

* Band of the Spanish [[Order of Queen Maria Luisa]].{{sfn|Laemmert|1853|p=24}}
* Grand Cross of the Portuguese [[Order of the Immaculate Conception of Vila Viçosa]].{{sfn|Laemmert|1853|p=24}}
* Grand Cross of the Portuguese [[Order of Saint Isabel]].{{sfn|Laemmert|1853|p=24}}
* Insignia of the Austrian [[Order of the Starry Cross]].{{sfn|Laemmert|1853|p=24}}
* Insignia of the Bavarian [[Order of Saint Elizabeth]].{{sfn|Laemmert|1853|p=24}}

